data-triple-N3.o: "The Gaulish (also Gallic) language is an extinct Celtic language that was spoken by the Gauls, a Celtic people who inhabited the region known as Gaul from the Iron Age to the Roman period. It was historically spoken through what are now mainly France, Northern Italy, Switzerland, Belgium, Luxembourg and western Germany before being supplanted by Vulgar Latin and various Germanic languages from around the 4th century onwards."@en
